change directory to "Venus" directory
"git log" will show all history on this directory
(Mosh has some commit on it)

Note: we copy the venus folder to our project,
      this folder has a ".git" file itself (find by:ls -a)
      so we have the history of Mosh commits by that file!
      actually they are two separate repository ! (nested repository)
      we can merge them! but we want to store them separately.
      so if we just use "add ." we get warning:
                                                  You've added another git repository inside your current repository.
                                                  hint: Clones of the outer repository will not contain the contents of
                                                  hint: the embedded repository and will not know how to obtain it.
                                                  hint: If you meant to add a submodule, use:

solution: we should add this directory as "SUBMODULE", it means
          The main repository keeps its own history
          The submodule also keeps its  own history
          The submodule’s commits do not become part of the main repository’s history
          The main repository only records submodule added on which commit!

Note: we should move the folder outside of the project
      because the command is cloning the folder to make it submodule
      we put the "Venus" folder on the ~/Venus src/section_3/Venus
      then use:
      git -c protocol.file.allow=always submodule add ~/Venus src/section_3/Venus

now to see this nested repository history
we change the directory to it (cd/src/section_3/Venus)
and use
"git log"                       or
"git log --oneline"

